One key to turn on/off or adjust volume Turn on the kids video games console at first, then turn right to increase the volume. Just turn left to OFF when you want to take a rest.

GV300S Retro Handheld Games Console Built-in 308 Classic Games Support TV Connecting with Handheld Controller Enjoy Large Screen of TV Connect your games console to TV with AV cable. Please confirm your TV has AV output and channel. Please note: this games console not supports HDMI.How to Connect to TV: The 2.5mm end is plugged into the console, the other two cables (RCA) plugged into the two jacks on TV. Make sure that the cable plug is connected to the corresponding color socket. Then tune the TV to the corresponding AV channel. How to Connect to Handheld Controller ? Handles will automatically match after being plugged in the battery (2*AAA, not included). The first one to make a match is P1 controller if you buy another handle. P1 handle means it can control the games console.Failure signal: controllers LED and link LED flash, then remove handle battery and replace. Successful signal: controllers and link LED are always on. The handle LED also flashes on work.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So cute and fun
reviews.reviewText: I got this for my nephew and we won best aunt and uncle award haha. He LOVED it and I enjoyed “testing” it for him too. Great little machine

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I got this for my son really, but it has so many games I forgot about! The quality of the screen is nice even though it weighs nothing. Super cool gift for kids or adults really 😂☺️

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I got this for my child for Christmas and it stopped working in February- right after the return date. Very disappointed with this product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 8, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I am a big retro gamer, got this because of how cute it is, and very happy with my purchase, My only issue is it has very bad screen tear on side scrolling games, I didn't see other reviewers mention it, maybe it's just my unit but the whole screen has a wave randomly when playing games that scroll from left to right. Besides that I love it! It's a cool little device for what it is, and the battery life is great I haven't charged it for a month.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewText: My daughter loved it and played with it the majority of the way home. (8 hour trip) I also played it a little myself.All you have to do is put rechargeable batteries into the controller and you’re good to go. It’s got games like Mario, Spiderman, etc.
